The paper deals with the problem of safe robot planning in the presence of humans, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed in the paper involves using predictive models of human motion, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also use Bayesian reasoning to modulate the robot's predictions based on the confidence in the model, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing human motion using computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and ensuring safety through control systems (cs.SY).
